 placeholder that you might give to another human being вЂ‹if you wanted to explain to вЂ‹them how to use the template you're providing. вЂ‹Let's look at this example. вЂ‹I'm giving it the same preamble for the template pattern. вЂ‹I'm still using capitalize words. вЂ‹I'm still using Markdown вЂ‹to try to get this formatted in a way that I want. вЂ‹This case, it's going to create headings wherever I have вЂ‹these hashtags and so вЂ‹what I'm doing is I'm saying bio and name. вЂ‹I'm going to paste in information about вЂ‹a history of Vanderbilt and I would like вЂ‹to get a list of people from that history of Vanderbilt. вЂ‹I want the names of the people and then I want вЂ‹an executive summary for вЂ‹each person and a full description for each person. вЂ‹Now, I'm stating that вЂ‹my executive summary is a one-sentence summary. вЂ‹You notice my placeholder is more than вЂ‹just go and talk about this person. вЂ‹I'm actually putting constraints on what I want there. вЂ‹I want one sentence that summarizes вЂ‹this person's role as described in вЂ‹the information I just gave вЂ‹and then for a full description, вЂ‹I say I want a one paragraph summary. вЂ‹Now, you can imagine you could go and вЂ‹capitalize a complex set of instructions, вЂ‹a one paragraph summary that only considers вЂ‹their history as part of Vanderbilt before 1800s. вЂ‹Now I haven't actually tested that one out, вЂ‹but I suspect it would actually work. вЂ‹But the key thing to note is I'm giving it вЂ‹more than just a sample match. вЂ‹I'm actually giving it a match on summary, вЂ‹go and create a summary here, вЂ‹but I'm also putting constraints. вЂ‹What it should be, it has to be вЂ‹a one paragraph summary or a one-sentence summary. вЂ‹This is like a power of вЂ‹the template pattern is that we can have вЂ‹complex instructions in the placeholders that we're вЂ‹actually going and replacing. вЂ‹Now I'm going to take a look. вЂ‹I patched it quite a lot of information. вЂ‹This is what we get as a result, вЂ‹is we get the headings as we had before with the name. вЂ‹That'll make sense but then if we вЂ‹look at the executive summary, вЂ‹it's exactly one sentence. вЂ‹It's not only filling in the template, вЂ‹but it's filling it in with вЂ‹the rules that we've described in the template. вЂ‹Now we've got a one-sentence summary вЂ‹in the executive summary, вЂ‹and then the full description we've вЂ‹got a one paragraph description. вЂ‹It goes through this for every single person that it вЂ‹extracts from the information that I give it. вЂ‹The template pattern is a way to help you вЂ‹get the output that you want in the format вЂ‹you want and you can вЂ‹use the placeholders in really sophisticated ways. вЂ‹They can be something that вЂ‹can semantically extract information. вЂ‹I can dump a bunch of information in and say, вЂ‹I want to know the people. вЂ‹Then it has to understand who are the people in this box, вЂ‹this bucket of information that's just been dumped вЂ‹in and has to be able to extract the people. вЂ‹I can say, I want a summary of each person, вЂ‹but it has to be one paragraph. вЂ‹You can have instructions and вЂ‹constraints on these placeholders. вЂ‹You can also have sophisticated things. вЂ‹We could have said, for вЂ‹example what is the role of each of вЂ‹these people in the history of вЂ‹Vanderbilt and it could describe their role. вЂ‹The placeholder can not only format the information, вЂ‹it cannot only do simple extracting and matching, вЂ‹but it can also do sophisticated things, вЂ‹they can follow rules or вЂ‹do things that would be really time-consuming вЂ‹for a human-like take and extract вЂ‹information that would require a human to вЂ‹read through and understand and then put it in. вЂ‹We're saying create вЂ‹a one-sentence summary of this person. вЂ‹Well, if I was going to have an assistant do that, вЂ‹they'd have to go read all the information and вЂ‹then make a list of all the people for вЂ‹each person I have to write first вЂ‹the one-sentence summary to try to вЂ‹capture everything about that person. вЂ‹Then they have to go write a one paragraph summary. вЂ‹That's really fast, really вЂ‹sophisticated intelligence that it's using вЂ‹in the key to getting the output that we вЂ‹want from it is using that template proud. вЂ‹We're saying this is the format that вЂ‹you're going to give it to me in this is вЂ‹exactly where everything goes and here are вЂ‹these really sophisticated rules вЂ‹in the placeholders to help you decide what goes in, вЂ‹how it gets formatted, what to exclude. вЂ‹It's a really powerful pattern for getting вЂ‹information in the format that you need and вЂ‹getting the right information put into that template.\"}